2026-04-14 07:55:04,037 INFO RLM iteration 2/50
Reasoning: We have inspected the workbook. The 'Open' sheet contains IDs in column C (index 3) and column K (index 11). The mapping from IDs to Names is in the 'Productivity' sheet, where column A holds IDs and column B holds the corresponding Names. To make the replacement dynamic (so future additions are automatically handled), we will write a VLOOKUP formula into every cell of columns C and K for all data rows (starting after the header row, which is row 3). The formula will be:

    =IFERROR(VLOOKUP(C4, Productivity!$A:$B, 2, FALSE), C4)

for column C and similarly for column K. This formula returns the Name if the ID is found; otherwise it leaves the original cell value unchanged. After writing the formulas we will save the workbook to the output directory, run `recalculate()` to evaluate formulas, reload the file with `data_only=True`, and verify a few sample cells to ensure they contain the expected Names (or original values when no match). Finally we will submit the path to the output spreadsheet.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from openpyxl.utils import get_column_letter
import os

# Paths
input_path = "/sandbox/input/input_spreadsheet/1_105-24_init.xlsx"
output_dir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/"
output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, "1_105-24_init.xlsx")

# Load workbook for editing
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)

# Ensure target sheets exist
open_ws = wb["Open"]
prod_ws = wb["Productivity"]

# Determine the last row with data in Open sheet (skip header row 3)
max_row = open_ws.max_row

# Columns to replace: C (3) and K (11)
col_indices = {3: "C", 11: "K"}

# Write VLOOKUP formulas for each data row (starting at row 4)
for row in range(4, max_row + 1):
    for col_idx, col_letter in col_indices.items():
        cell = open_ws.cell(row=row, column=col_idx)
        # Build formula string referencing the current cell
        # Use absolute column for lookup range
        formula = f"=IFERROR(VLOOKUP({col_letter}{row}, Productivity!$A:$B, 2, FALSE), {col_letter}{row})"
        cell.value = formula

# Save to output path
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate formulas (LibreOffice fallback)
await recalculate(output_path)

# Reload with data_only to verify a few cells
wb_check = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_check = wb_check["Open"]

# Print sample of rows 4-6 for columns C and K after recalculation
print("Verification sample (rows 4-6, columns C and K after recalculation):")
for r in range(4, 7):
    c_val = ws_check.cell(row=r, column=3).value
    k_val = ws_check.cell(row=r, column=11).value
    print(f"Row {r}: C={c_val!r}, K={k_val!r}")

# Submit the output spreadsheet path
SUBMIT(output_spreadsheet=output_path)
```

